f="tryout.php" target="_blank">click on this link</a>, you'll get a nice table. It's a square of digits between 1 and 9. The numbers given are the sums of each line and the two diagonals. You have to calculate the missing digits, concatenate them to one single string in row-major and submit them: 
<p class="challenge_1" style="text-align:center;">&quot;http://bright-shadows.net/challenges/programming/looping/solution.php?solution=&quot;+number string</p>You have 3 seconds to do this challenge.
<div class="challenge_mono_1" style="text-align:center;"><pre style="margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:10pt;">
+-Square------+-Rows----------------+-Cols----------------+-Diagonals----+
|  a b c d e  |  Row 1 = a+b+c+d+e  |  Col 1 = a+f+k+p+u  |  Diagonal 1  |
|  f g h i j  |  Row 2 = f+g+h+i+j  |  Col 2 = b+g+l+q+v  |  = a+g+m+s+y |
|  k l m n o  |  Row 3 = k+l+m+n+o  |  Col 3 = c+h+m+r+w  |              |
|  p q r s t  |  Row 4 = p+q+r+s+t  |  Col 4 = d+i+n+s+x  |  Diagonal 2  |
|  u v w x y  |  Row 5 = u+v+w+x+y  |  Col 5 = e+j+o+t+y  |  = u+q+m+i+e |
+-------------+---------------------+---------------------+--------------+
</pre></div>
